criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Hospitalization for a first episode of Cerebrovascular Accident less than six months
             old, or nth stroke less than six months old, with no previous sequelae;

          -  Able to walk at least 10m without stopping, with or without technical assistance, but
             without human assistance, under supervision;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Palliative or life-threatening situation;

          -  A patient whose guardian or trustee is not readily available to provide information
             about the patient

          -  Neuro-cognitive disorder that prevents understanding of instructions, as determined by
             the clinician;

          -  Severe speech or language disorder that prevents the protocol from being carried out
             correctly;

          -  Hemineglect;

          -  Any previously known pathology altering the gait pattern, at the clinician's
             discretion (recent neurological, traumatological or orthopaedic pathologies, etc.);

          -  Visual disorder preventing viewing of the video;

          -  Hearing disorder preventing comprehension.
